Outbreak statistics
Species Equidae
Apparent morbidity rate **
Apparent mortality rate **
Apparent case fatality rate 33.33 percent
Proportion susceptible animals lost* **
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction
and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Vectors; Contact
with wild species
Epidemiological comments: Cases reported have all been near forested
areas with some areas also being near rivers. The Ministry of Health
conducts vector control activities in the affected areas. The
increase in mosquitoes has been reported countrywide. All samples
submitted to the Reference Laboratory have been tested for West Nile
virus with negative results.

Control measures
Measures applied: Control of arthropods; Quarantine; Vaccination in
response to the outbreak (s)

Administrative division STANN CREEK
Species Equidae
Total Vaccinated 19
Details Modified live virus vaccine strain TC-83

Administrative division BELIZE
Species Equidae
Total Vaccinated 40
Details Modified live virus vaccine strain TC-83

Administrative division CAYO
Species Equidae
Total Vaccinated 500
Details Modified live virus vaccine strain TC-83

Administrative division ORANGE WALK
Species Equidae
Total Vaccinated 559
Details Polyvalent inactivated vaccine

No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Laboratory name and type: National Veterinary Services Laboratory
(NVSL), United States (OIE's Reference Laboratory)

Species Equidae
Test IgM-capture ELISA
Test date 28 Aug 2009
Result Positive

Species Equidae
Test Plaque reduction neutralisation test (PRN)
Test date 21 Aug 2009
Result Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

